.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.22" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose \- Compile a compose\-like spec into a single Slurm job using Enroot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Compile a compose\-like specification into one Slurm batch job that launches one or more services through Enroot and Pyxis inside a single allocation. Use up for the normal run, and use config, validate, inspect, preflight, and prepare when adapting or debugging a spec.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBvalidate\fR
Validate a compose spec without submitting a job. See hpc\-compose\-validate(1).
.TP
\fBrender\fR
Render the generated sbatch script. See hpc\-compose\-render(1).
.TP
\fBprepare\fR
Prepare imported and customized runtime images. See hpc\-compose\-prepare(1).
.TP
\fBpreflight\fR
Check cluster prerequisites on the submission host. See hpc\-compose\-preflight(1).
.TP
\fBinspect\fR
Inspect the normalized runtime plan. See hpc\-compose\-inspect(1).
.TP
\fBconfig\fR
Render the fully interpolated effective config. See hpc\-compose\-config(1).
.TP
\fBup\fR
Submit, watch, and stream logs in one command. See hpc\-compose\-up(1).
.TP
\fBsubmit\fR
Submit a job and optionally watch it. See hpc\-compose\-submit(1).
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
Show tracked scheduler state and log locations. See hpc\-compose\-status(1).
.TP
\fBstats\fR
Show tracked runtime metrics and step stats. See hpc\-compose\-stats(1).
.TP
\fBartifacts\fR
Export tracked artifact bundles after a run. See hpc\-compose\-artifacts(1).
.TP
\fBlogs\fR
Print tracked service logs. See hpc\-compose\-logs(1).
.TP
\fBps\fR
Show tracked per\-service runtime state. See hpc\-compose\-ps(1).
.TP
\fBwatch\fR
Watch a tracked job in a live terminal UI. See hpc\-compose\-watch(1).
.TP
\fBcancel\fR
Cancel a tracked Slurm job. See hpc\-compose\-cancel(1).
.TP
\fBdown\fR
Cancel a tracked job and clean tracked state. See hpc\-compose\-down(1).
.TP
\fBrun\fR
Run a one\-off command in one service environment. See hpc\-compose\-run(1).
.TP
\fBnew\fR
Write a starter compose file from a built\-in template. See hpc\-compose\-new(1).
.TP
\fBcache\fR
Inspect and prune cached image artifacts. See hpc\-compose\-cache(1).
.TP
\fBjobs\fR
List tracked jobs under the current repo tree. See hpc\-compose\-jobs(1).
.TP
\fBclean\fR
Remove old tracked job directories. See hpc\-compose\-clean(1).
.TP
\fBcontext\fR
Print resolved project\-local settings context. See hpc\-compose\-context(1).
.TP
\fBsetup\fR
Create or update the project\-local settings file. See hpc\-compose\-setup(1).
.TP
\fBcompletions\fR
Generate shell completions. See hpc\-compose\-completions(1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.TP
\fB-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
Print version.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBcompose.yaml\fR
Fallback compose specification file when \-f or \-\-file is omitted and the active context does not provide one.
.TP
\fB<compose\-file\-dir>/hpc\-compose.sbatch\fR
Default rendered batch script path written by submit when \-\-script\-out is not set.
.TP
\fB${SLURM_SUBMIT_DIR:\-$PWD}/.hpc\-compose/\fR
Tracked job metadata, logs, metrics, and artifact state written after submission.
.TP
\fB~/.cache/hpc\-compose\fR
Default cache root for imported and prepared image artifacts when x\-slurm.cache_dir is unset.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBHOME\fR
Used to resolve the default cache path and default configuration locations.
.TP
\fBPATH\fR
Used to resolve external commands such as enroot, sbatch, srun, squeue, sacct, sstat, and scancel.
.TP
\fBENROOT_CONFIG_PATH\fR
Consulted during preflight when checking Enroot configuration discovery.
.TP
\fBXDG_CONFIG_HOME\fR
Consulted during preflight when checking Enroot configuration discovery.
.TP
\fBSLURM_SUBMIT_DIR\fR
Used by rendered jobs when resolving the tracked runtime directory on the host.
.TP
\fBSLURM_JOB_ID\fR
Used in tracked runtime paths and in artifact export directory expansion after submission.
.TP
\fBHPC_COMPOSE_PRIMARY_NODE and related HPC_COMPOSE_* runtime variables\fR
Injected into services inside submitted jobs to describe allocation metadata and resume state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
